avor of retaining the estate tax in some form, have proposed amending the tax to exempt farm assets up to $4 million for individuals, and $8 million for couples.  This would exempt 98%+ of farms from being subject to estate tax.  The revenue impact from this would be relatively small, as the number of farms affected by estate taxes is just not that high, as compared to total number of estates affected by the tax. Similar proposals have been made to protect small business assets.<br>
<br>
