<br>
Some quick questions, that will allow you to confirm this:  <br>
<br>
1.) in a free floating currency exchange system, what's the normal reaction of the market for a nation that runs trade deficits?<br>
<br>
2.) given that currencies are not asset based, what is the likely direction for a currency's valuation, if the participants in the forex markets see that government in a continual pattern of deficit spending?<br>
<br>
3.) If from all indications, the direction of a currency's value vis a vis other currencies is down, what do interest rates have to be high, or low, to attract capital flows into that country to continually finance that country's growth in public debt?  Bonus: what are the implications above for domestic interest rates?<br>
